OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773194861
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FThe Home Secretary has approved a
OL,7,Frequest from the Metropolitan Police
OL,8,Fto ban a pro-Palestinian march planned
OL,9,Ffor Sunday "to prevent serious public
OL,10,Fdisorder".
OL,12,FThe annual Al Quds Day march in London
OL,13,Fhad drawn criticism over apparent
OL,14,Fbacking for the Iranian regime after
OL,15,Fits organisers expressed support for
OL,16,Fthe country's late leader Ayatollah
OL,17,FAli Khamenei.
OL,19,FSeveral counter-protests had also been
OL,20,Fplanned for the day.
OL,26,@qD@LOUrD@IO]
