FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773194862
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FThe Metropolitan Police said previous
OL,7,FAl Quds Day marches resulted in
OL,8,Farrests for supporting terrorist
OL,9,Forganisations and antisemitic hate
OL,10,Fcrimes.
OL,12,FIn a statement, the force said: "The
OL,13,Fdecision to ban it this year is purely
OL,14,Fbased on a risk assessment of this
OL,15,Fspecific protest and counter-protests
OL,16,F` we do not police taste or decency or
OL,17,Fprefer one political view over
OL,18,Fanother, but we will do everything we
OL,19,Fcan to reduce violence and disorder."
OL,26,@tD@aOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
