OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773194862
OL,3,CHome Secretary grants police request
OL,4,Cto ban Al Quds Day march
OL,6,FThe decision follows calls from Labour
OL,7,Fand Conservative MPs to ban the march.
OL,9,FEarlier on Tuesday, courts minister
OL,10,FSarah Sackman said people expressing
OL,11,Fsupport for "the malign regime in
OL,12,FIran" should not be "on the streets of
OL,13,FLondon calling for hate and hostility
OL,14,Fagainst this country".
OL,16,FShadow Home Office minister Alicia
OL,17,FKearns also called for the march to be
OL,18,Fcancelled, saying there was "no place
OL,19,Fin our country for the celebration of
OL,20,Fterrorists".
OL,26,@sD@MOUtD@EO]tD@UOUvD@UO]zD@]OU|D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
